1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,500
This is the Inclusive Certification Coach —
an accessibility-first learning coach for enterprise teams.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:09,500
It's built as eight cooperating agents, grounded in
Microsoft Foundry IQ, with every claim cited.

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:15,000
The clean landing page invites the learner
to set a goal and build a plan.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Three tabs sit at the top:
Learn, Manager view, and How it works.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
In the sidebar I pick my certification — AZ-204 —
my role, and how I work best.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,000
I note ADHD and trouble focusing,
then choose Build my plan.

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,500
The Curator retrieves grounded content
and builds a cited learning path.

8
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:41,500
Each module shows recommended hours,
an accommodation note, and its source citation.

9
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:48,500
Behind it, the Study Plan Generator schedules
short, focus-friendly blocks with breaks.

10
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:55,000
Every step is grounded in retrieved knowledge-base
chunks — no hallucinated facts.

11
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:01,000
With Listen mode on, the Accessibility Narrator
turns the result into a spoken script.

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:07,000
There's a real player — play, pause,
choose a voice, and adjust the speed.

13
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Symbols and abbreviations are read as words,
so it's screen-reader friendly.

14
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Next, the Calendar Negotiator fits
study into my real week.

15
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:23,000
It finds genuine gaps between meetings
and books study blocks into them.

16
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:29,000
I can adjust the daily cap, block length,
and preferred time — it re-books instantly.

17
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:36,000
If the week is too full, it pushes back with
evidence instead of pretending it fits.

18
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Now the readiness check —
and I choose how I'm tested.

19
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:48,000
I can pick exactly which topics
to be quizzed on, and how many questions.

20
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The questions are realistic, exam-style
scenarios — not trivia about the guide.

21
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Or I can switch to Teach-it-back and
explain a concept in my own words.

22
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:09,000
It grades my understanding, names what
I covered, and flags what's missing.

23
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Then it asks one Socratic follow-up
aimed at the biggest gap.

24
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Let me answer the quick questions
and submit them.

25
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:32,000
The Assessment Agent scores me
and reports my weak areas.

26
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Then the Orchestrator reasons over my
score, weak areas, and attempt history.

27
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:48,000
It decides one of three actions: advance,
loop back, or escalate to a human.

28
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Here it loops me back — to study
only the areas I got wrong.

29
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:03,000
One click starts a focused refresher,
re-quizzing just those topics.

30
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
The loop is real reasoning,
not a fixed script.

31
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:13,000
If I need support, the Advocate drafts
a note to my manager for me.

32
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:21,000
I choose whether to share my accessibility
profile — it's private by default.

33
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Redaction is enforced in code, so the
model can't leak what it never saw.

34
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:36,000
The draft shows exactly what it shares
and what it keeps private.

35
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Nothing is sent without my approval.

36
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:47,000
The Manager view rolls the whole team
up for a people manager.

37
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Manager Insights reasons over each learner's
progress against the readiness threshold.

38
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Profiles of learners who haven't opted in
stay redacted here too.

39
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Finally, How it works
makes the reasoning legible.

40
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:14,000
It logs every agent step, the chunks it
retrieved, and their relevance scores.

41
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:22,000
And it shows the orchestrator's signals
weighed and alternatives rejected.

42
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Deterministic guardrails keep it safe —
stalled learners always reach a human.

43
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Grounded, reliable, and accessibility-first —
backed by 72 of 72 eval checks.

44
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Thanks for watching.
